    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The function "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "udf_ValidEnergySource",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " is a scalar function in Microsoft SQL Server. Scalar functions return a single value and are used to encapsulate reusable logic that can be applied to individual rows in a query. This function is designed to determine the validity of an energy source based on certain criteria, which are not specified in the prompt but would involve checking against a predefined list or set of rules."
        }
      ]
    },
