          "type": "text",
          "text": "6. Performance Considerations"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Scalar functions can impact performance when used in large queries, especially if they are called repeatedly for each row in a result set. They are executed row-by-row, which can lead to slower performance compared to set-based operations. To mitigate this, ensure that the function logic is as efficient as possible and consider alternatives like inline table-valued functions if performance becomes an issue."
